The sample of Ag was analyzed by XRD with the results as shown in Fig. 1
                     . In the figure, the diffraction peaks at 2theta=38.5°, 44.5°, 64.5° represent the (111), (200), (220) planes of the face-centered-cubic structure of metallic silver, respectively, which indicates the AgNPs was successfully synthesized [21]. The binding energies of 368 and 374eV in the Ag 3d spectra (the inset of Fig. 2
                     ) of Ag@C nanocomposites are attributed to Ag 3d5/2 and Ag 3d3/2, which also well indicate the formation of metallic Ag [22].
